    "mainEntity":[
      {"@type":"Question","name":"How can I tell what tiles my opponent has in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Track tiles played, note which letters remain in the bag, and observe word choices. If they consistently avoid high-value positions or play only consonants, their rack likely contains the inverse. Combined with tile tracking (100 tiles total), you can narrow their holdings significantly by mid-game."}},
      {"@type":"Question","name":"What are common behavioral tells in competitive Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Hesitation before playing a short word suggests a weak rack. Quick confident plays indicate pre-planned sequences. Reaching toward the tile bag then pulling back means they considered exchanging. Studying one board area repeatedly reveals where they plan to play next."}},
